{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ea7abb2d-a786-4ec5-82da-d79548f49e58","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Update packages** — replace `xunit.runner.visualstudio` with `xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform`:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n   <!-- Add -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"2.9.3\" />\n   ```\n\n2. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests** with `dotnet test` as usual — it works with MTP when `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` is set.\n\n   You can also run the test project directly as an executable:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run --project YourTests.csproj\n   ```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- Keep `xunit` (or `xunit.core` + `xunit.assert`) at **2.9.3** — those don't change.\n- The runner package version should match your xunit version.\n- If you use `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`, you can **remove** it (MTP doesn't need it), though leaving it is harmless.\n- If you have a `.runsettings` file, most settings carry over, but review the [MTP docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform-intro) for any differences.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"12fe623f-dc6d-486f-9e1a-588902d3e6a9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":454,"requestId":"A03B:16E70A:BA629B:DA7AE5:69FE84F8"},"id":"126db3b7-ed54-4a3a-b27c-43d2d2670a7c","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:14.058Z","parentId":"84f54e4b-78d6-4d55-b7a0-4b6f08f5f25e"}
